Date: Sun, 12 Dec 2004 01:09:41 -0500 (EST)

 Telnet to that port does not work.  Telnet to port 1024 on that machine
 returns an immediate "Connection refused" message, not a long delay like a
 telnet to port 1025 does.  Is there something in particular that might
 lead to port 1025 being firewalled by itself?  It looks like it is used
 for Microsoft RPC and so might be firewalled to contain viruses.
 
