Subject: Re: all/7140: Bug report server used by Help Desk appears to be down
Date: Sat, 18 Dec 2004 05:02:58 -0500

 On Dec 17, Robby Findler wrote:
 > I think that I will wait for someone to make a server (and the spec)
 > and I'll make the bug report form send according to that spec.
 
 The spec is simply a POST query, like the following:
 
 originator=My+Name&replyto=my-email%40address.com&subject=Summary+of+my+problem&release=666&platform=windows-nt&severity=serious&class=sw-bug&description=The+description+of+the+problem%0D%0ASecond+line+of+description&how-to-repeat=A+short+sequence+of+steps%3A%0D%0A1.+first+step%0D%0A2.+second+one%0D%0A3.+last+one
 
 The fields that are currently used are:
 
   replyto
   originator (Originator)
   subject (Synopsis)
   severity (Severity)
   class (Class)
   release (Release)
   platform (Environment)
   description (Description)
   how-to-repeat (How-To-Repeat)
 
 I can easily extend this list.  The parenthesized labels are the Gnats
 fields that are put in the PR email.
 
 The reply is a simple HTML that either says that you should expect an
 answer or that there was an error.  If you can render the returned
 HTML it would be best since problems that result from places on the
 way (proxies, caches, firewalls) will be obvious.
 
 Anything else needed?
 
