Subject: Re: all/7140: Bug report server used by Help Desk appears to be down
Date: Sun, 19 Dec 2004 00:06:09 -0500

 Another problem -- you don't actually use post...  I have verified
 this by looking at the http log file, and you do actually fetch a url
 that contains the whole thing.  With actual bug report you will run
 into Apache's internal alarms for avoiding bogus huge urls.  (The url
 is currenly about 4kb).
 
 I'd guess that the `get-pure-port' on line 421 should change, but I
 don't know how things work exactly...
