 Seems like you got it right finally...  Sorry for not replying
 earlier, I spent most of the day fighting bureaucrats, then crashed.
 
 
 > Also, I think that you should drop that "try again" link from the
 > error message page.
 
 The two responses follow -- send me any edits you want and I'll put it
 in.  Or you can see the whole code in iplt/web/scripts/bug-report,
 it's very simple.
 
 ======================================================================
 (define (output-page)
   (make-page "Bug report submitted"
     `("Your PLT bug report has been submitted"
       (p)
       "To check on submitted reports, visit the bug report "
       (a ((href "http://bugs.plt-scheme.org/query/")) "query page")
       "."
       (p)
       "You should receive email confirmation of your report in 30 minutes"
       " or less.  The confirmation will be sent to"
       (p)
       (blockquote () (tt ((style "font-size:small")) ,replyto))
       (p)
       "If this email address is incorrect, or if you do not receive such"
       " confirmation, please report the problem to "
       (tt ((style "font-size:small")) "scheme@plt-scheme.org") ".")))
 
 (define (error-page)
   (make-page "Bug report error"
     `("An error occurred when submitting your PLT bug report"
       (p)
       "Please try submitting your report again, making sure your email"
       " address is correct."
       (p)
       (a ((href "http://bugs.plt-scheme.org/")) "Click here")
       " to submit a new report."
       (p)
       "If this problem persists, please send email to "
       (tt () "scheme@plt-scheme.org") ".")))
 ======================================================================
 
 
